WEBVTT

00:02.923 --> 00:05.005
[ CHURCH BELL TOLLING ]

00:10.431 --> 00:11.802
YOU'RE LATE.

00:11.802 --> 00:13.224
I KNOW.

00:13.224 --> 00:14.685
SHE'S WORRIED.
WELL, I'M HERE NOW.

00:18.849 --> 00:22.143
April:
IN TRAUMA, WE'RE CONCERNED
WITH ONE OVERRIDING QUESTION...

00:23.694 --> 00:25.196
...HOW DID THIS HAPPEN?

00:25.196 --> 00:26.567
I DIDN'T WANT YOU
TO SEE ME YET.

00:26.567 --> 00:27.608
I KNOW.

00:27.608 --> 00:31.322
TATIANA, YOU LOOK...

00:31.322 --> 00:33.114
SO BEAUTIFUL.

00:33.114 --> 00:35.706
WHAT WAS
THE MECHANISM OF INJURY?

00:35.706 --> 00:38.659
HOW DO WE SEE PAST THE MESS
AND CONFUSION OF THE TRAUMA

00:38.659 --> 00:41.041
TO FIGURE OUT
WHAT THE DAMAGE ACTUALLY IS?

00:41.041 --> 00:43.624
INFINITE POSSIBILITIES

00:43.624 --> 00:46.547
PUT THE PATIENT
ON THE TABLE IN FRONT OF YOU.

00:46.547 --> 00:51.302
NOW YOU HAVE TO FIGURE OUT --
WILL THEY LIVE?

00:51.302 --> 00:54.135
WILL YOU BE ABLE TO SAVE THEM?

00:54.135 --> 00:55.266
[ SIGHS ]

00:55.266 --> 00:57.268
OR ARE THEY A LOST CAUSE?

00:57.268 --> 00:59.730
NO SHARED ASSETS,
NO CHILDREN,

00:59.730 --> 01:03.274
AND, OF COURSE, THERE'S A SOLID
POST-NUPTIAL AGREEMENT IN PLACE.

01:03.274 --> 01:07.188
WITH NOTHING TO CONTEST, IT'S
JUST ABOUT SIGNING THE PAPERS.

01:08.689 --> 01:11.242
THE PLACES TO INITIAL AND SIGN
ARE ALL CLEARLY MARKED.

01:11.242 --> 01:14.285
RED TABS FOR INITIALS,
BLUE TABS FOR SIGNATURES.

01:14.285 --> 01:17.868
EVERY PART OF A TRAUMA TELLS
A DIFFERENT PIECE OF THE STORY.

01:17.868 --> 01:20.661
THIS IS ONE OF THE SIMPLER
DIVORCES I'VE SEEN, ACTUALLY.

01:20.661 --> 01:23.754
AND UNTIL YOU LOOK
AT EACH AND EVERY INJURY...

01:27.298 --> 01:28.969
Nathan: SO, WHAT ARE YOU GONNA
DO? YOU GONNA SIGN THE PAPERS?

01:28.969 --> 01:30.671
April: WE HAVE TO PUSH,
AND WE HAVE TO FIGHT.

01:30.671 --> 01:32.883
Jackson: I'M NOT SURE
WE ARE WORTH FIGHTING FOR.

01:32.883 --> 01:34.515
[ TAPE REWINDING ]

01:34.515 --> 01:36.387
...YOU CAN'T SEE
WHAT WENT WRONG.

01:36.387 --> 01:37.478
AT WORK?

01:37.478 --> 01:38.979
THAT'S WHERE YOU DECIDE
TO DO THIS?!

01:38.979 --> 01:41.142
YOU WANT
TO LOWER YOUR VOICE?

01:41.142 --> 01:42.603
WHAT DOES IT MATTER
HOW LOUD MY VOICE IS

01:42.603 --> 01:45.606
WHEN 35 PEOPLE JUST SAW ME
GET SERVED WITH DIVORCE PAPERS

01:45.606 --> 01:47.688
IN THE MIDDLE
OF THE EMERGENCY ROOM?!

01:47.688 --> 01:49.440
[ ELEVATOR BELL DINGS ]
I AM SORRY ABOUT THAT,
ALL RIGHT?

01:49.440 --> 01:51.031
THAT WAS NOT SUPPOSED
TO HAPPEN.
[ SIGHS ]

01:51.031 --> 01:52.823
HE WAS SUPPOSED TO
TALK TO YOU AFTER YOU
WERE DONE WITH WORK.

01:52.823 --> 01:55.326
IT'S ONLY BEEN FOUR WEEKS.
FOUR, JACKSON.

01:55.326 --> 01:57.618
IS THAT -- THAT'S ALL
THE COUNSELING YOU COULD
HANDLE BEFORE BAILING?

01:57.618 --> 01:59.450
YOU SAID
YOU WANTED TO TRY!

01:59.450 --> 02:00.831
WE DID TRY.

02:00.831 --> 02:02.543
IT DIDN'T WORK.
IT DIDN'T GET US ANYWHERE.

02:02.543 --> 02:04.625
WE HAVE THE SAME EXACT FIGHT
OVER AND OVER AGAIN,

02:04.625 --> 02:06.006
AROUND IN CIRCLES.

02:06.006 --> 02:07.458
I'M TELLING YOU --
IT'S NOT WORKING.

02:07.458 --> 02:09.960
THEN WHY ARE WE EVEN BOTHERING
WITH COUNSELING?!

02:09.960 --> 02:11.882
WHAT IS
THE POINT OF COUNSELING

02:11.882 --> 02:14.555
IF YOU'RE JUST GONNA SUDDENLY,
WITHOUT EVEN TALKING, JUST --

02:14.555 --> 02:16.717
OH, COME ON.
ALL WE DO IS TALK, APRIL.

02:16.717 --> 02:18.389
SO, WHAT? YOU JUST --
YOU JUST SERVE ME PAPERS?

02:18.389 --> 02:19.680
JUST LIKE THAT?

02:19.680 --> 02:23.354
DO YOU HAVE ANY IDEA
WHAT A SLAP IN THE FACE THIS IS?

02:28.569 --> 02:30.110
HOW LONG?!

02:30.110 --> 02:32.032
HOW LONG
HAVE I BEEN SITTING ON A COUCH

02:32.032 --> 02:33.113
DISCUSSING MY MARRIAGE

02:33.113 --> 02:34.575
WITH SOMEONE
WHO HAS ALREADY CHECKED OUT?

02:34.575 --> 02:35.696
THAT'S NOT
WHAT I WAS DOING.

02:35.696 --> 02:37.117
NO, I JUST WANT TO KNOW
WHEN IT HAPPENED.

02:37.117 --> 02:39.990
WHEN DID YOU DECIDE
THAT YOU WERE DONE?

02:39.990 --> 02:41.081
[ TAPE REWINDING ]

02:41.081 --> 02:42.623
SHE DIDN'T SAY THAT.
YEAH, SHE DID.

02:42.623 --> 02:44.205
WHEN DID SHE SAY THAT?
[ CAR ALARM CHIRPS ]

02:44.205 --> 02:45.746
SHE'S BEEN SAYING IT
FOR THREE WEEKS NOW.

02:45.746 --> 02:47.748
WE SHOULDN'T BE
HAVING SEX.

02:47.748 --> 02:50.000
I HARDLY THINK
OUR SEX LIFE IS OUR PROBLEM.
[ CAR ALARM CHIRPS ]

02:50.000 --> 02:51.171
I DON'T THINK
IT'S A PROBLEM.

02:51.171 --> 02:52.052
IT JUST --
IT GETS IN THE WAY.

02:52.052 --> 02:53.254
IN THE WAY OF WHAT?

02:53.254 --> 02:55.095
YOU'RE JUST HEARING
WHAT YOU WANT TO HEAR.

02:55.095 --> 02:57.968
I'M HEARING WHAT OUR
THERAPIST IS TELLING
US, AND YOU'RE NOT.

02:57.968 --> 03:00.721
IT'S LIKE WE'RE SITTING
IN ON TWO COMPLETELY
DIFFERENT SESSIONS.

03:00.721 --> 03:02.473
[ CAR ALARM CHIRPS ]
THAT'S JUST OFFENSIVE.

03:02.473 --> 03:03.764
WHAT'S OFFENSIVE IS YOU KEEP
CHOOSING TO IGNORE --

03:03.764 --> 03:05.566
I'M NOT IGNORING ANYTHING!

03:05.566 --> 03:07.017
SEE? YOU CAN'T EVER
TAKE RESPONSIBILITY.

03:07.017 --> 03:08.229
YOU NEVER APOLOGIZE
FOR ANYTHING.

03:08.229 --> 03:11.572
[ CAR ALARM CHIRPS ]
I APOLOGIZE ALL THE TIME.

03:11.572 --> 03:12.653
NOT FOR THE THINGS
THAT MATTER.

03:12.653 --> 03:13.864
WHAT DO I HAVE
TO APOLOGIZE FOR, JACKSON?

03:13.864 --> 03:15.656
I AM HERE,
AND I'M TRYING.

03:15.656 --> 03:17.157
I WANT TO MAKE THIS WORK.

03:17.157 --> 03:18.158
[ CAR ALARM CHIRPS ]
STOP!

03:18.158 --> 03:20.241
WILL YOU JUST --
DON'T TOUCH IT.

03:20.241 --> 03:21.372
[ CAR ALARM CHIRPS ]

03:21.372 --> 03:23.624
SORRY.

03:23.624 --> 03:26.957
[ CAR DOOR OPENS, CLOSES ]

03:26.957 --> 03:28.959
[ INHALES DEEPLY ]

03:28.959 --> 03:30.631
[ TAPE REWINDING ]

03:30.631 --> 03:33.003
NOW, REMEMBER,
ONCE WE REMOVE THESE BANDAGES,

03:33.003 --> 03:35.676
THERE'S GONNA BE SOME --
SOME REDNESS, SOME SWELLING.

03:35.676 --> 03:39.300
SO...DID YOU TALK TO APRIL
LAST NIGHT?

03:39.300 --> 03:40.641
I DID.

03:40.641 --> 03:42.723
AND?
HOW'D IT GO?

03:42.723 --> 03:45.436
NOT, UH --
NOT EXACTLY AS I EXPECTED.

03:45.436 --> 03:47.438
OH, GOD.
SHE TOOK IT THAT HARD?

03:47.438 --> 03:51.352
OR SHE DIDN'T BECAUSE...

03:51.352 --> 03:52.483
YOU DIDN'T ASK HER,
DID YOU?

03:52.483 --> 03:53.774
TATIANA.
YOU'RE KIDDING ME.

03:53.774 --> 03:55.115
IT'S REALLY NOT THAT SIMPLE.
SURE, IT IS.

03:55.115 --> 03:57.027
YOU JUST SAY, "THIS ISN'T
WORKING FOR ME ANYMORE.

03:57.027 --> 03:59.029
I'M NOT HAPPY.
I WANT A DIVORCE."

03:59.029 --> 04:00.491
KNOCK, KNOCK!
[ Chuckling ] HEY.

04:00.491 --> 04:02.953
OH. WELL, YOU READY
FOR THE UNVEILING?

04:02.953 --> 04:04.915
FOUR YEARS' HARD WORK,
AVERY.

04:04.915 --> 04:06.997
WELL, I'M JUST THE SURGEON.
TATIANA'S HAD THE HARDEST JOB.

04:06.997 --> 04:09.370
THIS GUY.
ALWAYS SWEET-TALKING.

04:09.370 --> 04:11.292
43 SURGERIES, 4 YEARS,

04:11.292 --> 04:14.795
3 MONTHS,
1 WEEK, AND 4 DAYS.

04:14.795 --> 04:16.377
CAN'T BELIEVE
THIS IS THE LAST TIME

04:16.377 --> 04:17.798
YOU'LL BE UNWRAPPING
MY FACE.

04:17.798 --> 04:19.970
[ TELEPHONE RINGS ]

04:19.970 --> 04:21.472
OKAY.

04:21.472 --> 04:23.884
LET'S DO IT.

04:23.884 --> 04:25.225
[ SIGHS ]

04:25.225 --> 04:28.599
WAIT. I'M...

04:28.599 --> 04:30.311
I DON'T THINK
I'LL BE ABLE TO LOOK.

04:30.311 --> 04:32.313
HEY, WHAT KIND OF HACK
DO YOU THINK I AM?

04:32.313 --> 04:33.944
YOU ARE GOING
TO WANT TO SEE THIS.

04:33.944 --> 04:35.446
TRUST ME.

04:35.446 --> 04:38.569
♪♪

04:38.569 --> 04:40.531
[ TAPE REWINDING ]

04:40.531 --> 04:42.202
HOW'S MEREDITH?

04:42.202 --> 04:45.616
SHE'S GOOD, CONSIDERING
IT'S HER FIRST WEEK OF RECOVERY.

04:45.616 --> 04:47.998
GOOD.

04:47.998 --> 04:49.790
WHAT ARE YOU UP TO?
[ CHUCKLES ]

04:49.790 --> 04:50.791
[ MONITOR BEEPING ]
YOU'RE JUST...

04:50.791 --> 04:52.913
MM-HMM?
YOU'RE SO...

04:52.913 --> 04:55.586
REMEMBER HOW OUR THERAPIST SAID
THAT WE SHOULD BE MORE DIRECT

04:55.586 --> 04:58.178
WITH WHAT WE WANT?
OH.

04:58.178 --> 05:00.090
Maybe you should be more direct
with what you want.

05:00.090 --> 05:04.475
I HAVE AN HOUR
UNTIL MY I&D CASE.

05:04.475 --> 05:06.687
I'M HEADING
TO THE ON-CALL ROOM...

05:06.687 --> 05:07.888
TAKE A LITTLE NAP.

05:07.888 --> 05:09.690
OH, YEAH?
YEAH.

05:09.690 --> 05:11.432
TOO BAD
YOU WON'T BE GETTING ANY SLEEP.

05:11.432 --> 05:14.194
♪♪

05:17.738 --> 05:19.279
[ TAPE REWINDING ]

05:19.279 --> 05:21.201
I DON'T WANT TO TALK,
BECAUSE YOU KNOW WHAT?

05:21.201 --> 05:22.493
I KNOW
WHAT YOU'RE GONNA SAY!

05:22.493 --> 05:24.074
YOU'RE GONNA SAY
"YOU LOVE ME, BUT"!

05:24.074 --> 05:25.946
YOU DON'T KNOW
WHAT I'M GOING TO SAY!

05:25.946 --> 05:28.078
OH, I'M PRETTY SURE I DO.
IT DOESN'T MATTER!
YOU DON'T!

05:28.078 --> 05:30.711
FINE! FINE.
THEN JUST GO AHEAD.

05:30.711 --> 05:31.872
COME --
SAY IT.

05:31.872 --> 05:33.504
[ SIGHS ]

05:33.504 --> 05:35.215
OH, MY GOD, JACKSON!

05:35.215 --> 05:38.258
GOD! PLEASE!
WOULD YOU JUST SAY IT?!

05:41.632 --> 05:43.343
YOU'RE RIGHT. I WAS.

05:43.343 --> 05:44.925
I WAS GONNA ASK YOU
FOR A DIVORCE

05:44.925 --> 05:46.767
WHEN WE WENT FOR DINNER,

05:46.767 --> 05:48.228
AND THEN AGAIN
WHEN WE STAYED IN FOR DINNER...
YEAH.

05:48.228 --> 05:49.390
...AND THEN THINGS HAPPENED.

05:49.390 --> 05:50.521
YEAH, WELL,
WE HAD SEX, JACKSON.

05:50.521 --> 05:51.642
THAT'S WHAT HAPPENED.
WE HAD SEX.

05:51.642 --> 05:53.524
I WAS CLEAR ABOUT THIS.

05:53.524 --> 05:55.065
MY MIND WAS MADE UP.

05:55.065 --> 05:57.398
I KNEW WHAT WAS BEST FOR ME --
MOVING FORWARD,

05:57.398 --> 05:58.689
NO MATTER HOW HARD.

05:58.689 --> 06:01.361
I KNEW THERE WERE THINGS
THAT WE COULDN'T REPAIR.

06:01.361 --> 06:02.743
I KNEW WHAT I HAD TO DO.

06:02.743 --> 06:05.325
AND IT'S NOT CLEAR
FOR ME ANYMORE.

06:05.325 --> 06:09.289
THIS -- WHEN I LOOK AT YOU
AND I STOP THINKING...

06:09.289 --> 06:13.704
WHEN I LET MYSELF
JUST BE WITH YOU...

06:13.704 --> 06:15.335
ALL I'M SAYING IS,
I DON'T THINK

06:15.335 --> 06:17.377
THAT I WANT
WHAT I WANTED ANYMORE.

06:17.377 --> 06:19.710
AND WHAT I WANT...

06:19.710 --> 06:21.922
[ SIGHS ]
WHAT?

06:25.005 --> 06:26.847
I WANT YOU.

06:30.390 --> 06:31.682
[ TAPE REWINDING ]

06:47.948 --> 06:49.239
YOU GUYS HAD SEX.
YEAH, WE DID, TOO.

06:49.239 --> 06:50.871
IT'S MESSY.
STOP RUNNING AWAY FROM ME.

06:50.871 --> 06:53.163
CALLIE, YOU AND ARIZONA,
BEFORE YOU GUYS SPLIT,

06:53.163 --> 06:55.456
YOU DID THE COUNSELING THING,
RIGHT?

06:55.456 --> 06:56.667
[ TAPE REWINDING ]

06:56.667 --> 06:58.919
[ BOTH BREATHING HEAVILY ]

07:13.894 --> 07:16.647
♪♪

07:34.665 --> 07:36.747
[ SIGHS ]

07:41.211 --> 07:42.843
[ DOOR CLOSES ]

07:54.895 --> 07:56.016
[ TAPE REWINDING ]

07:56.016 --> 07:57.898
I MEAN, AN HOUR WAIT
FOR A TABLE?

07:57.898 --> 08:00.400
IT'S RIDICULOUS.
I'M HUNGRY NOW.

08:00.400 --> 08:03.193
OH.
THIS WAS
SUCH A BETTER IDEA.

08:03.193 --> 08:05.405
PLACE LOOKS NICE.

08:05.405 --> 08:07.528
CHANGED SOME THINGS AROUND,
HUH?

08:07.528 --> 08:09.239
SOME NEW PILLOWS.

08:09.239 --> 08:10.531
I LIKE THOSE.

08:10.531 --> 08:12.242
NO, YOU DON'T.
YOU HATE THROW PILLOWS.

08:12.242 --> 08:13.874
[ CHUCKLES ] I REALLY DO.
YEAH, I KNOW.

08:13.874 --> 08:15.245
I'M SORRY.
YOU WANT SOMETHING TO DRINK?

08:15.245 --> 08:16.076
YEAH.

08:19.079 --> 08:20.420
OH, MY GOD.

08:20.420 --> 08:22.502
THEY GAVE US
SO MANY FORTUNE COOKIES.

08:22.502 --> 08:24.044
I LOVE FORTUNE COOKIES!

08:24.044 --> 08:25.756
I KNOW.
I ASKED FOR EXTRA.

08:27.548 --> 08:31.011
I'M SORRY AGAIN ABOUT
LAST NIGHT GETTING CUT SHORT.

08:31.011 --> 08:32.723
I GET IT.
IT'S OKAY. IT'S FINE.

08:32.723 --> 08:35.135
YEAH, I KNOW.

08:40.140 --> 08:42.062
AND...

08:42.062 --> 08:43.774
LOOK AT THAT.

08:51.241 --> 08:52.953
AMEN.

08:54.825 --> 08:56.366
THANK YOU FOR WAITING.

08:56.366 --> 08:58.418
MM-HMM.

08:58.418 --> 09:00.711
YOU WANT TO KNOW
WHAT I WAS PRAYING FOR?

09:00.711 --> 09:02.713
[ SIGHS ]
NO, THAT'S ALL RIGHT.

09:02.713 --> 09:04.875
THROW PILLOWS.

09:04.875 --> 09:07.467
THOUSANDS OF THEM
JUST RAINING FROM THE SKY.
[ LAUGHS ]

09:07.467 --> 09:09.009
I DO NOT UNDERSTAND
THEIR PURPOSE.

09:09.009 --> 09:10.220
THEY HAVE SO MANY PURPOSES.

09:10.220 --> 09:11.632
THEY DON'T.
THEY'RE LIKE A POP OF COLOR.

09:11.632 --> 09:13.053
THEY JUST GET IN THE WAY. I JUST
DON'T UNDERSTAND WHAT THE...

09:13.053 --> 09:14.264
YOU, LIKE, PROP UP
YOUR ARMS AND YOUR FEET.

09:14.264 --> 09:15.636
MOVING THEM AROUND THE HOUSE.
PLUS, IT LOOKS NICE.

09:15.636 --> 09:16.637
[ CHUCKLES ]
YOU'RE FUNNY.

09:16.637 --> 09:18.639
IT'S GOOD, RIGHT?
IT'S REALLY GOOD.

09:18.639 --> 09:20.440
TOLD YOU
YOU'D LIKE THIS PLACE.
I CAN'T BELIEVE
I NEVER NOTICED IT.

09:20.440 --> 09:22.733
I PROBABLY ORDERED TAKEOUT
EVERY NIGHT WHILE YOU WERE GONE.

09:22.733 --> 09:25.525
AND I DIDN'T REALIZE THIS PLACE
WAS RIGHT AROUND THE CORNER.

09:25.525 --> 09:26.817
WOW. OKAY.

09:26.817 --> 09:29.449
WHAT?
WE JUST SAT DOWN TO EAT.

09:29.449 --> 09:32.282
I-I THOUGHT
WE WERE HAVING A NICE TIME.
WE ARE.

09:32.282 --> 09:33.694
SO WHY ARE YOU GONNA RUIN IT
BY PICKING A FIGHT?

09:33.694 --> 09:35.535
NO, I'M NOT.

09:35.535 --> 09:37.577
I WASN'T PICKING A FIGHT.
I WAS JUST TALKING CHINESE FOOD.

09:37.577 --> 09:39.369
AND JORDAN.
AND TAKEOUT.

09:39.369 --> 09:40.871
I AM NOT THE ONE
GETTING DEFENSIVE.

09:40.871 --> 09:43.003
AND I AM?
LOOK...

09:43.003 --> 09:44.334
I DID NOT COME HERE
TO FIGHT TONIGHT.

09:44.334 --> 09:46.416
OKAY.

09:46.416 --> 09:48.879
OKAY?

09:48.879 --> 09:50.130
OKAY.

09:57.427 --> 09:59.930
SO, WHY DID YOU
COME HERE?

10:04.855 --> 10:06.647
THROW PILLOWS, OBVIOUSLY.

10:06.647 --> 10:07.567
[ BOTH LAUGH ]

10:07.567 --> 10:09.780
[ SIGHS ]

10:09.780 --> 10:11.942
I SAW YOU HAD A, UM,
NASAL SEPTUM RECONSTRUCTION

10:11.942 --> 10:13.153
UP ON THE BOARD TODAY.

10:13.153 --> 10:15.495
IS THAT FOR TATIANA?
UH, YEAH. HER FINAL SURGERY.

10:15.495 --> 10:17.908
SHE'S COME SUCH A LONG WAY.
YOU SHOULD BE SO PROUD.

10:17.908 --> 10:19.539
I AM.

10:19.539 --> 10:23.333
I MEAN, I-I WILL BE ONCE IT
ALL KIND OF COMES TOGETHER.

10:23.333 --> 10:24.875
MM-HMM.

10:24.875 --> 10:27.297
I'VE PERFORMED SO MANY
SURGERIES ON HER, YOU KNOW,

10:27.297 --> 10:30.380
THAT HER FACE IS
JUST THIS ROAD MAP, YOU KNOW,

10:30.380 --> 10:33.513
OF AN INCREDIBLE JOURNEY
THAT WE'VE BEEN ON TOGETHER.

10:35.756 --> 10:37.257
I'M RAMBLING.
I'LL STOP.

10:41.892 --> 10:43.894
WE REALLY SHOULD TALK,
THOUGH.

10:43.894 --> 10:46.526
WE ARE TALKING.

10:46.526 --> 10:48.188
YEAH, I MEAN...

10:48.188 --> 10:49.439
REALLY TALK.

10:49.439 --> 10:50.570
ABOUT US.

10:50.570 --> 10:53.153
MM-HMM.

10:53.153 --> 10:55.655
OBVIOUSLY IT'S NOT EASY,
YOU KNOW?

10:55.655 --> 10:58.078
I DO THINK IT'S RIGHT.

10:58.078 --> 10:59.199
IF YOU'RE STRUGGLING
THIS MUCH,

10:59.199 --> 11:00.580
MAYBE THAT SHOULD
TELL YOU SOMETHING.

11:00.580 --> 11:02.282
MAYBE YOU SHOULD STOP BEFORE
YOU SAY WHATEVER IT IS --

11:02.282 --> 11:04.374
WE NEED TO TALK ABOUT
GETTING A DIVORCE.

11:07.087 --> 11:09.710
APRIL...

11:09.710 --> 11:11.171
[ Sighing ] OKAY.

11:13.593 --> 11:14.674
COME ON. DON'T --

11:14.674 --> 11:17.137
[ SIGHS ]

11:17.137 --> 11:18.889
WE'RE NOT EVEN
LIVING TOGETHER.

11:20.350 --> 11:22.602
OKAY, THIS IS THE FIRST
SUBSTANTIAL CONVERSATION

11:22.602 --> 11:23.974
WE'VE HAD
IN, WHAT, MONTHS?

11:23.974 --> 11:25.896
WELL, THAT IS YOUR CHOICE
AND NOT MINE,

11:25.896 --> 11:27.397
'CAUSE I'VE BEEN HERE.

11:27.397 --> 11:28.648
I'VE BEEN WILLING
TO HAVE ANY CONVERSATION.

11:28.648 --> 11:30.230
DON'T DO THAT.

11:30.230 --> 11:32.442
DON'T BLAME ME.
I'M NOT BLAMING YOU.

11:32.442 --> 11:34.314
IT'S NOT BLAME.
IT'S JUST FACT.

11:34.314 --> 11:35.655
I WANT TO TALK TO YOU,

11:35.655 --> 11:37.157
BUT WE'RE HAVING
TWO DIFFERENT CONVERSATIONS

11:37.157 --> 11:39.239
'CAUSE I WANT TO WORK ON THINGS
AND YOU JUST WANT TO END THEM.

11:39.239 --> 11:40.951
I'M NOT BEING FLIP
ABOUT ANY OF THIS.

11:40.951 --> 11:43.583
YOU ACTUALLY BELIEVE
THAT I'M TAKING THIS LIGHTLY?

11:43.583 --> 11:45.495
IT JUST SEEMS LIKE
YOU ARE LOOKING FOR AN EXCUSE

11:45.495 --> 11:47.667
TO WALK AWAY INSTEAD
OF PUTTING IN ANY OF THE WORK --

11:47.667 --> 11:50.210
YOU LEFT ME!

11:50.210 --> 11:52.212
YOU WALKED AWAY!

11:52.212 --> 11:54.674
YOU -- YOU RAN HALFWAY ACROSS
THE WORLD! HOW CO--

11:54.674 --> 11:57.547
'CAUSE I WAS DYING, JACKSON!

11:57.547 --> 12:01.341
SAMUEL DIED, AND I DIED!

12:01.341 --> 12:04.935
UNTIL JORDAN, UNTIL I WAS
ABLE GO OVER THERE AND --

12:04.935 --> 12:07.477
AND WHAT?

12:07.477 --> 12:10.851
YOU THINK I WAS SOMEHOW
JUST FINE AFTER SAMUEL?

12:10.851 --> 12:12.612
YOU DON'T THINK
I WAS DYING, TOO?

12:12.612 --> 12:14.775
NO. NO, OKAY?

12:14.775 --> 12:16.616
YOU WEREN'T.
NOT LIKE ME.

12:16.616 --> 12:17.657
YOU WERE COPING.

12:17.657 --> 12:19.199
YOU -- YOU WERE OKAY.

12:19.199 --> 12:20.660
I COULDN'T EVEN...

12:20.660 --> 12:22.702
AND THEN I FOUND SOMETHING.

12:22.702 --> 12:26.286
I FOUND SOMETHING OVER THERE
THAT I NEEDED SO BADLY!

12:26.286 --> 12:28.668
AND I THOUGHT
THAT YOU UNDERSTOOD THAT!

12:28.668 --> 12:29.830
I WASN'T COPING.

12:31.501 --> 12:33.253
I WAS COVERING.

12:33.253 --> 12:34.674
FOR YOU.
I WAS...

12:34.674 --> 12:37.087
TO TAKE CARE OF YOU.

12:37.087 --> 12:40.300
AND NOW YOU'RE PUNISHING ME
OVER AND OVER

12:40.300 --> 12:44.184
BECAUSE I DARED TO TAKE
THINGS INTO MY OWN HANDS

12:44.184 --> 12:46.596
BECAUSE I RECOGNIZED
THE SPIRAL I WAS FALLING INTO,

12:46.596 --> 12:48.188
AND I WENT AND DID
SOMETHING ABOUT IT?

12:48.188 --> 12:49.389
I WAS PUTTING YOU FIRST.

12:49.389 --> 12:51.231
THAT'S WHAT YOU DO
IN A MARRIAGE!

12:51.231 --> 12:53.313
OR I GUESS
THAT'S NOT WHAT YOU DO.

12:53.313 --> 12:56.526
I DON'T --
I TOOK CARE OF MYSELF
SO THAT I WOULD SURVIVE!

12:56.526 --> 12:59.319
AND ALL THAT DOES
IS MAKE YOU ANGRY.

12:59.319 --> 13:01.201
[ SCOFFS ]
LOOK AT YOU.

13:01.201 --> 13:02.742
WHAT...

13:02.742 --> 13:04.244
WHAT IS IT, JACKSON?

13:04.244 --> 13:07.617
WHAT -- WHAT PISSES YOU OFF
SO MUCH --

13:07.617 --> 13:10.911
THAT I CHOSE TO GO AFTER
THE THING THAT I NEEDED TO HEAL

13:10.911 --> 13:13.293
OR THAT THE THING I NEEDED
WASN'T YOU?

13:13.293 --> 13:14.624
THE THING
THAT I NEEDED WAS YOU!

13:20.971 --> 13:22.472
I SURVIVED.

13:22.472 --> 13:25.225
YOU SURVIVED.

13:25.225 --> 13:26.806
BUT I DO NOT THINK
WE CAN SURVIVE THIS.

13:26.806 --> 13:29.269
[ SIGHS ]

13:29.269 --> 13:31.191
NO, I'M NOT GETTING DIVORCED,
JACKSON, OKAY?

13:31.191 --> 13:32.812
NO ONE IN MY FAMILY
HAS EVER BEEN DIVORCED.

13:32.812 --> 13:34.985
EVERYONE IN MY FAMILY
HAS.

13:34.985 --> 13:36.937
SOMETIMES MARRIAGES
JUST DON'T WORK OUT.

13:36.937 --> 13:39.319
IT'S NOT JUST
THE HARDER THING SOMETIMES.

13:39.319 --> 13:40.400
MAYBE SOMETIMES
IT'S HEALTHIER.

13:40.400 --> 13:42.242
I'M NOT GIVING UP ON US.
I WON'T.

13:42.242 --> 13:44.074
YOU ALREADY DID.
MY GOD!

13:44.074 --> 13:45.405
STOP SAYING THAT!
YOU TAKE FOR GRANTED

13:45.405 --> 13:46.786
THAT I'M JUST GONNA WAIT
FOR YOU,

13:46.786 --> 13:49.829
AND WAIT AND WAIT,
NO MATTER WHAT!

13:49.829 --> 13:52.662
BUT DIVORCE IS NOT SOME
DIRTY WORD, APRIL, NOT FOR ME.

13:52.662 --> 13:53.954
IN FACT, RIGHT NOW,
IT'S A LIGHT

13:53.954 --> 13:54.915
AT THE END
OF A REALLY DARK TUNNEL.

13:57.797 --> 13:59.589
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?
REALLY?

13:59.589 --> 14:01.721
THAT'S WHAT
THIS HAS BEEN TO YOU?

14:01.721 --> 14:04.094
OH, I'M SO SORRY I KEPT YOU
LOCKED AWAY IN THIS PRISON CAMP!

14:04.094 --> 14:06.096
HEY!
YOU JUST WANT TO END IT,
HUH?

14:06.096 --> 14:08.058
IS THAT WHAT YOU'RE SAYING?
THAT'S NOT WHAT I SAID.

14:08.058 --> 14:09.389
YOU JUST WANT TO
PRETEND LIKE THIS --
WELL, WHAT ARE YOU SAYING?

14:09.389 --> 14:11.351
YOU WOULD KNOW
IF YOU WOULD LISTEN!
I AM LISTENING!

14:11.351 --> 14:13.603
WHAT ARE YOU DOING?
I'M THROWING COOKIES!

14:13.603 --> 14:14.895
WHY?!
BECAUSE!

14:14.895 --> 14:16.356
BECAUSE WHY?
I DON'T KNOW!

14:16.356 --> 14:17.817
YOU'RE BEING RIDICULOUS!
STOP!
I KNOW!

14:17.817 --> 14:19.319
STOP.
I KNOW!

14:19.319 --> 14:20.110
[ SIGHS ]

14:21.821 --> 14:23.443
WHAT...

14:23.443 --> 14:24.784
WHAT IS HAPPENING TO US?

14:24.784 --> 14:26.486
I DON'T...KNOW.

14:26.486 --> 14:28.488
[ SIGHS ]

14:28.488 --> 14:29.659
HOW DID WE GET TO THIS?

14:29.659 --> 14:32.162
I DON'T KNOW.

14:32.162 --> 14:35.455
HOW DO WE MAKE IT STOP?

14:38.548 --> 14:41.881
♪♪

14:56.566 --> 14:57.607
MM.
WAIT.

14:57.607 --> 14:58.778
WAIT. WHAT?
WE SHOULD...

14:58.778 --> 14:59.980
PROBABLY NOT DO THIS.

14:59.980 --> 15:01.281
PROBABLY NOT --
NOT A GOOD IDEA.

15:01.281 --> 15:02.322
NO. YEAH, ABSOLUTELY.

15:02.322 --> 15:03.823
IT'S NOT A GOOD IDEA.
ALL RIGHT.

15:03.823 --> 15:05.325
YEAH, YEAH.
OKAY.

15:19.589 --> 15:20.750
YOU KNOW WHAT THEY CALL THAT?
DIVORCE.

15:20.750 --> 15:23.383
AND IT WASN'T AN ULTIMATUM.
I GAVE YOU A CHOICE.

15:23.383 --> 15:24.384
[ TAPE REWINDING ]

15:24.384 --> 15:25.925
WHERE'S
MY MAXILLOFACIAL CONSULT?

15:25.925 --> 15:27.637
-ON THE WAY.
-G.C.S. IS 9.

15:27.637 --> 15:29.429
PUPILS ARE ASYMMETRIC.
WE NEED TO ESTABLISH AN AIRWAY.

15:29.429 --> 15:31.141
WHAT DO YOU GOT?
HE FELL 20 FEET.

15:31.141 --> 15:33.473
C6-7 UNSTABLE FRACTURE.

15:33.473 --> 15:35.815
HE'S BREATHING ON HIS OWN,
BUT HE NEEDS A SECURE AIRWAY.

15:35.815 --> 15:37.607
OKAY.
LARYNGOSCOPE, PLEASE.

15:37.607 --> 15:39.559
WAIT. WHY ARE YOU HERE?
AIRWAY. YOU PAGED ME.

15:39.559 --> 15:41.021
I THOUGHT YOU WERE
GOING TO THE AIRPORT,

15:41.021 --> 15:42.482
FLYING TO JORDAN
WITH APRIL.

15:42.482 --> 15:43.613
YEAH. N-NO.

15:43.613 --> 15:46.276
UM, YEAH, I DECIDED
NOT TO GO, ACTUALLY.

15:46.276 --> 15:49.829
UH, SCOPE, PLEASE.
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

15:49.829 --> 15:51.781
IS THIS FLIGHT 2703
TO JORDAN?

15:51.781 --> 15:53.783
I NEED TO GET ON THAT PLANE.
I'M SORRY, SIR,

15:53.783 --> 15:55.375
BUT ONCE THE DOORS
ARE OFFICIALLY CLOSED,

15:55.375 --> 15:56.576
THERE'S REALLY NOTH--
PLEASE, OKAY?

15:56.576 --> 15:57.917
MY WIFE'S ON THAT FLIGHT.

15:57.917 --> 15:59.539
I JUST NEED TO GET TO MY WIFE,
SO IF YOU COULD JUST --

15:59.539 --> 16:01.211
OH, MY GOD.
THAT IS SO SWEET.

16:01.211 --> 16:02.792
SO YOU'LL OPEN THE DOORS?
NO.

16:02.792 --> 16:04.044
ARE YOU KIDDING ME RIGHT NOW?
I'M SORRY.

16:04.044 --> 16:05.255
THERE'S NOTHING I CAN DO.

16:05.255 --> 16:07.887
YOUR PLANE'S LEAVING.
WHAT?

16:07.887 --> 16:11.551
[ AIRPLANE DEPARTING ]

16:12.932 --> 16:14.764
[ TAPE REWINDING ]

16:14.764 --> 16:16.726
WHAT THE HELL DO YOU
MEAN THAT OWEN'S NOT
GONNA BE THERE WITH YOU?

16:16.726 --> 16:18.688
I'M NOT GONNA BE THERE ALONE.
THERE'S A WHOLE UNIT OF US.

16:18.688 --> 16:20.980
WE WORK TOGETHER.
WE'RE -- WE'RE FRIENDS.

16:20.980 --> 16:23.103
I MEAN, WE'RE MORE THAN THAT.
WE'RE LIKE FAMILY.

16:23.103 --> 16:24.734
WE HAVE EACH OTHER'S BACKS.
WE GET EACH OTHER.

16:24.734 --> 16:26.696
MM-HMM.
LIKE I DON'T GET YOU, RIGHT?

16:28.698 --> 16:30.280
COME WITH ME.
COME ON.

16:30.280 --> 16:32.612
I-IT'S NOT TOO LATE.
I CAN MAKE A COUPLE PHONE CALLS.

16:32.612 --> 16:33.953
NO.
WE ALWAYS NEED
MORE SURGEONS OVER THERE.

16:33.953 --> 16:36.036
APRIL, NO.
MY ANSWER HASN'T CHANGED.

16:36.036 --> 16:38.418
IF YOU COULD JUST SEE
WHAT IT'S LIKE OVER THERE,

16:38.418 --> 16:39.459
THE WORK WE DO.

16:39.459 --> 16:41.171
IT'S IMPORTANT.

16:41.171 --> 16:42.582
IT'S IMMEDIATE.
IT'S ESSENTIAL.

16:42.582 --> 16:43.833
THERE'S NO FILTER.

16:43.833 --> 16:46.836
THERE'S NO TIME
TO EVEN...

16:46.836 --> 16:49.049
SO OFTEN AROUND HERE,

16:49.049 --> 16:50.220
WE, LIKE,
WALK THROUGH LIFE

16:50.220 --> 16:51.551
AND GET CAUGHT UP
WITH ALL THIS STUFF.

16:51.551 --> 16:52.632
THERE'S NO STUFF
OVER THERE.

16:52.632 --> 16:54.094
EVERY DAY, EVERY PATIENT
HAS PURPOSE.

16:54.094 --> 16:55.345
IT HAS MEANING.

16:55.345 --> 16:58.558
[ SIGHS ]

16:58.558 --> 17:00.850
I-I WANT YOU TO KNOW IT
THE WAY THAT I KNOW IT.

17:00.850 --> 17:02.642
AND I CAN'T JUST PICK UP
AND GO.

17:02.642 --> 17:04.314
I HAVE COMMITMENTS.

17:04.314 --> 17:05.485
I HAVE PEOPLE.
WHO? WHO?

17:05.485 --> 17:07.067
WHAT PEOPLE
DO YOU HAVE HERE

17:07.067 --> 17:08.698
THAT WOULD PREVENT YOU
FROM COMING OVERSEAS WITH ME?

17:08.698 --> 17:10.070
PATIENTS.

17:10.070 --> 17:11.151
I MEAN, I'M NOT WILLING

17:11.151 --> 17:13.153
TO JUST ABANDON PEOPLE
THAT DEPEND ON ME.

17:13.153 --> 17:15.615
AND I AM?

17:15.615 --> 17:18.458
KIND OF.

17:18.458 --> 17:20.420
KIND OF, YEAH.

17:20.420 --> 17:22.122
[ TAPE REWINDING ]
I'M STILL GETTING
A LOT OF NECROSIS.

17:22.122 --> 17:23.623
I'M AFRAID THAT [SIGHS]

17:23.623 --> 17:26.876
THE STUPID PARAMEDIAN FOREHEAD
FLAP IS DYING -- AGAIN.

17:26.876 --> 17:28.468
THIS IS THE SECOND ONE.

17:28.468 --> 17:30.930
I DO NOT KNOW
WHY THIS IS HAPPENING.

17:30.930 --> 17:32.972
I HARVESTED TWO BLOOD VESSELS
THIS TIME

17:32.972 --> 17:34.514
JUST TO MAKE SURE
THAT IT WOULDN'T --

17:34.514 --> 17:35.725
[ SIGHS ]

17:35.725 --> 17:37.137
I WAS SO CAREFUL
TO AVOID CLOTTING,

17:37.137 --> 17:40.059
BUT IT'S STILL JUST...

17:40.059 --> 17:41.391
[ SIGHS ]

17:41.391 --> 17:43.603
I'M SORRY.
WE'LL FIGURE THIS OUT.

17:43.603 --> 17:45.445
THIS ISN'T YOUR FAULT,
YOU KNOW.

17:45.445 --> 17:48.238
MAYBE MY FACE JUST DOESN'T LIKE
FOREHEAD FLAPS. [ CHUCKLES ]

17:48.238 --> 17:50.029
HEY.

17:50.029 --> 17:51.451
YOU WILL FIGURE THIS OUT.

17:51.451 --> 17:52.992
YOU ALWAYS DO.

17:52.992 --> 17:55.285
IT'S NOT LIKE WE HAVEN'T
HAD SETBACKS BEFORE.

17:55.285 --> 17:56.576
YEAH.

17:56.576 --> 17:58.037
I KNOW.
IT'S JUST...

17:58.037 --> 18:01.541
JUST CRAPPY 'CAUSE THIS ONE'S
HAPPENING RIGHT BEFORE CHRISTMAS

18:01.541 --> 18:05.755
WHEN YOUR WIFE'S OFF BEING SOME
KIND OF SUPERHERO IN A DESERT.

18:05.755 --> 18:08.668
AND, I MEAN...

18:08.668 --> 18:11.551
I WAS AROUND FOR WHAT HAPPENED
THIS TIME LAST YEAR...

18:11.551 --> 18:13.803
WHEN YOU LOST SAMUEL.

18:13.803 --> 18:16.476
AND I KNOW, WELL...

18:16.476 --> 18:18.678
THINGS HAVE TO BE TOUGH
FOR YOU RIGHT NOW.

18:22.272 --> 18:23.433
[ TAPE REWINDING ]

18:23.433 --> 18:25.895
COME ON! JUST GIVE ME A SIGNAL!
JUST...

18:25.895 --> 18:28.278
DAMN IT!
[ SIGHS ]

18:28.278 --> 18:30.280
COME ON, COME ON,
COME ON, COME ON, COME ON.

18:34.284 --> 18:36.236
COME ON!

18:36.236 --> 18:38.658
[ SIGHS ]

18:40.540 --> 18:42.412
[ TAPE REWINDING ]
DO YOU NEED
MORE ANESTHETIC?

18:42.412 --> 18:43.793
NO, I'M OKAY.

18:43.793 --> 18:45.295
I HEARD
YOU WERE DOWN HERE.

18:45.295 --> 18:46.956
WHAT HAPPENED, BABY?

18:46.956 --> 18:48.878
IT'S NOTHING.
IT WAS JUST AN ACCIDENT AT HOME.

18:48.878 --> 18:52.632
HAVE YOU HEARD FROM APRIL?
DID SHE CALL YOU TODAY?

18:52.632 --> 18:54.344
SHE'S BUSY OVER THERE,
YOU KNOW.

18:54.344 --> 18:57.427
I MEAN, SHE PROBABLY DOESN'T
EVEN REALIZE WHAT DAY IT IS.

18:57.427 --> 18:59.759
HOW CAN I HELP YOU?

18:59.759 --> 19:01.851
WHAT DO YOU NEED?

19:01.851 --> 19:03.813
YOU KNOW, I COULD USE
MORE LIDOCAINE WITH EPI,

19:03.813 --> 19:04.814
IF YOU WOULDN'T MIND.

19:04.814 --> 19:06.436
I'LL FIND SOME.

19:10.530 --> 19:12.442
[ TAPE REWINDING ]

19:18.538 --> 19:20.990
[ GRUNTING ]

19:20.990 --> 19:22.872
AAH! GOD!

19:22.872 --> 19:24.784
[ BREATHES SHARPLY ]

19:51.861 --> 19:53.653
IT IS SO GOOD TO BE BACK.

19:53.653 --> 19:54.694
[ TAPE REWINDING ]

19:54.694 --> 19:56.446
APRIL.
I'M -- I'M NOT WORKING.

19:56.446 --> 19:58.408
I'M -- I'M JUST --
I'M NOT READY TO WORK YET.

20:03.413 --> 20:05.875
HEY.
I'M GONNA HEAD IN TO WORK.

20:05.875 --> 20:06.916
YOU HAVE BREAKFAST?

20:12.332 --> 20:15.094
YOU KNOW, YOU HAVEN'T BEEN
TO CHURCH IN A WHILE.

20:15.094 --> 20:17.887
WHAT DO YOU SAY
WE GO TOGETHER?

20:17.887 --> 20:19.048
HUH?

20:19.048 --> 20:22.932
HEY.

20:22.932 --> 20:25.845
LOOK AT ME, SWEETHEART.

20:25.845 --> 20:28.938
HMM?

20:28.938 --> 20:30.310
WHAT IF WE...

20:30.310 --> 20:32.442
[INHALES DEEPLY]

20:32.442 --> 20:34.023
TRY AGAIN?

20:34.023 --> 20:36.155
HMM?

20:36.155 --> 20:38.027
LET'S TRY
FOR ANOTHER BABY.

20:40.530 --> 20:41.991
WHY WOULD YOU SAY THAT?

20:41.991 --> 20:43.663
NO, I JUST WANT --

20:43.663 --> 20:44.864
WHAT?!

20:44.864 --> 20:46.456
WHAT DO YOU WANT?

20:46.456 --> 20:48.828
APRIL...
SCREW YOU.

20:48.828 --> 20:51.581
[ Voice breaking ] SCREW YOU
FOR EVEN SUGGESTING THAT.

20:51.581 --> 20:53.333
SCREW YOU.

20:53.333 --> 20:54.924
OKAY.

20:54.924 --> 20:56.876
[ SOBS ]

20:56.876 --> 20:59.429
ALL RIGHT.
[ SNIFFLES ]

20:59.429 --> 21:01.761
I'LL GO.

21:01.761 --> 21:03.763
[ CHAIR CLATTERS ]

21:03.763 --> 21:05.805
I'LL JUST GO IN TO WORK.

21:05.805 --> 21:07.847
[ SNIFFLES ]

21:07.847 --> 21:11.100
[ CLEARS THROAT ]

21:11.100 --> 21:12.982
[ CRYING ]

21:15.695 --> 21:17.657
GET OFF OF ME!
OKAY, JUST CALM DOWN.
I KNOW.

21:17.657 --> 21:19.198
GET OFF!
WARREN!

21:19.198 --> 21:21.160
I WAS JUST MARKING HER FACE
FOR SURGERY.

21:21.160 --> 21:23.162
THAT MARKER REEKS!
I DON'T WANT IT NEAR MY FACE!
ALL RIGHT, GUYS, UH...

21:23.162 --> 21:24.454
SHE KEEPS TRYING
TO TAKE OFF HER BANDAGES.

21:24.454 --> 21:26.245
I'M NOT DOING THIS ANYMORE!
I CAN'T! I'M DONE!

21:26.245 --> 21:27.997
ALL RIGHT, WARREN, WILSON,
GIVE US A MINUTE.

21:27.997 --> 21:29.369
HEY, TATIANA,
WHAT IS GOING ON?

21:29.369 --> 21:30.620
[ BREATHING RAPIDLY ]
WHAT IS IT?

21:30.620 --> 21:32.372
[ Voice breaking ]
I HAD A LIFE BEFORE THIS!

21:32.372 --> 21:34.123
I HAD A LIFE!

21:34.123 --> 21:36.676
THEN I WAS IN THE WRONG PLACE
AT THE WRONG TIME,

21:36.676 --> 21:39.919
AND NOW MY FACE
IS MELTED OFF OF MY FACE!

21:39.919 --> 21:41.921
IT'S BEEN
A YEAR AND A HALF,

21:41.921 --> 21:44.053
AND THERE'S SO MUCH MORE
TO GO.

21:44.053 --> 21:45.595
SO MANY MORE SURGERIES!

21:45.595 --> 21:46.766
AND WITH EACH ONE,
YOU GET BETTER.

21:46.766 --> 21:48.558
THIS IS MY LIFE NOW --

21:48.558 --> 21:51.731
THESE WALLS,
THIS BED, YOU!

21:51.731 --> 21:53.142
I WANT IT BACK.

21:53.142 --> 21:56.315
I WANT IT ALL BACK
TO WHO I WAS BEFORE.

21:56.315 --> 21:57.487
I KNOW.

21:57.487 --> 21:59.198
I KNOW.

21:59.198 --> 22:01.441
[ TAPE REWINDING ]

22:01.441 --> 22:04.203
♪♪

22:12.291 --> 22:14.163
[ CLEARS THROAT ]
OH, HEY. GOOD MORNING.

22:14.163 --> 22:15.455
HEY, MORNING.
MORNING, SIR. YEAH.

22:15.455 --> 22:16.876
MM-HMM.

22:21.300 --> 22:23.383
[ SIGHS ]

22:23.383 --> 22:25.595
♪ WE'RE HAVING A BABY ♪
[ GIGGLES ]

22:25.595 --> 22:27.677
♪ WE'RE HAVING A BABY ♪

22:27.677 --> 22:29.639
♪ WE'RE HAVING A BABY ♪

22:30.810 --> 22:32.351
OOH. HEY.
WHAT YOU DOING?

22:32.351 --> 22:34.734
OH.
UM...

22:34.734 --> 22:36.686
[ HUMMING ]
WE'RE DANCING.

22:36.686 --> 22:38.478
DANCE.
RIGHT ON.

22:38.478 --> 22:39.939
RIGHT ON.

22:39.939 --> 22:41.110
[ HUMMING ]

22:42.361 --> 22:43.403
OH. HI.

22:43.403 --> 22:44.654
HI.

22:44.654 --> 22:46.245
WELL, WHO DIED?

22:46.245 --> 22:47.987
WHAT?!
NOBODY.

22:47.987 --> 22:50.700
WE'RE JUST DANCING.
I ONLY DANCE IT OUT
WHEN SOMETHING BAD HAPPENS.

22:50.700 --> 22:52.452
-OH.
-NOT TODAY.

22:52.452 --> 22:54.414
-DID SOMEONE --
-DID I LEAVE MY --

22:54.414 --> 22:55.625
WELL, ALL RIGHT!

22:55.625 --> 22:56.706
-MM-HMM.
-HEY.

22:56.706 --> 22:58.207
-MM-HMM.
-NO.

22:58.207 --> 22:59.959
[ LAUGHTER ]
[ HUMMING ]

23:01.801 --> 23:02.842
WHAT THE HELL?

23:04.714 --> 23:06.095
OH.

23:08.007 --> 23:09.388
[ Singsongy voice ] HEY.

23:09.388 --> 23:11.100
HEY!
[ LAUGHTER ]

23:11.100 --> 23:12.472
[ Normal voice ]
OH, ALL RIGHT. ALL RIGHT.

23:12.472 --> 23:14.013
WE CELEBRATING
THE NEW BABY?

23:14.013 --> 23:15.935
WHAT?
WAIT. WHAT?

23:15.935 --> 23:17.937
WHAT DID SHE SAY?
TORRES?

23:17.937 --> 23:19.398
WHAT --
WHAT DID YOU SAY?

23:19.398 --> 23:21.611
UH, WELL...

23:21.611 --> 23:22.942
I'm so sorry.

23:22.942 --> 23:26.115
WE ARE ACTUALLY
CELEBRATING A BABY.

23:26.115 --> 23:27.487
I AM PREGNANT.

23:27.487 --> 23:28.828
OH, MY GOD!

23:28.828 --> 23:30.079
-HOLY CRAP.
-YEAH, YEAH.

23:30.079 --> 23:31.741
[ LAUGHTER ]

23:31.741 --> 23:33.032
-CONGRATULATIONS.
-THANK YOU!

23:33.032 --> 23:34.413
-WHOO!
-CONGRATULATIONS!

23:34.413 --> 23:35.705
YEAH!

23:35.705 --> 23:37.336
HEY, HEY.

23:37.336 --> 23:39.539
THANK YOU!
THANK YOU!

23:39.539 --> 23:41.130
[ LAUGHTER ]

23:41.130 --> 23:42.632
WORK IT OUT.

23:42.632 --> 23:45.965
[ LAUGHTER ]

23:52.011 --> 23:53.432
IT'S ONE SMALL CONCESSION.
IT'S NOT SMALL.

23:53.432 --> 23:55.515
LOOK, WE ARE ABOUT
TO TELL MY PARENTS

23:55.515 --> 23:57.897
THAT WE GOT MARRIED,
ELOPED.

23:57.897 --> 24:00.480
THEY WANTED TO BE
AT MY WEDDING.

24:00.480 --> 24:02.191
THEY THOUGHT
THEY WERE AT MY WEDDING.

24:02.191 --> 24:03.442
I'M JUST NOT COMFORTABLE
WITH IT.

24:03.442 --> 24:04.484
I MEAN, YOU KNOW THAT.

24:04.484 --> 24:06.445
I KNOW
THAT YOU'RE NOT RELIGIOUS.

24:06.445 --> 24:09.238
SO WHY ARE YOU ASKING ME
TO LEAD YOUR FAMILY IN PRAYER?

24:09.238 --> 24:12.492
BECAUSE THEY'RE PREDISPOSED
TO NOT LIKE YOU.

24:12.492 --> 24:14.123
YOU'RE MARRYING
A RICH, HANDSOME SURGEON.

24:14.123 --> 24:16.075
[ Chuckling ] STOP IT.
I KNOW.

24:16.075 --> 24:17.787
WE EMBARRASSED THEM.

24:17.787 --> 24:19.038
AND WE WILL APOLOGIZE
FOR THAT.

24:19.038 --> 24:20.289
SINCERELY, OKAY?

24:20.289 --> 24:21.711
BUT I'M NOT GONNA CHANGE
WHO I AM

24:21.711 --> 24:23.172
JUST TO GET YOUR PARENTS
TO LIKE ME.
NO, NO, NO.

24:23.172 --> 24:25.044
NO, I DON'T WANT YOU
TO CHANGE WHO YOU ARE.

24:25.044 --> 24:27.296
YOU WANT ME TO LIE.
NO. COME ON.

24:27.296 --> 24:29.639
IT'S -- IT'S A GESTURE
OF GOOD FAITH.

24:29.639 --> 24:31.721
MY GESTURE OF GOOD FAITH

24:31.721 --> 24:34.594
IS BEING A WONDERFUL HUSBAND
TO THEIR BEAUTIFUL DAUGHTER.

24:34.594 --> 24:36.305
IT'S ONE DAY.

24:36.305 --> 24:38.437
ONE PRAYER.

24:38.437 --> 24:41.691
NOT LIKE I'M ASKING YOU
TO GO GET BAPTIZED.

24:41.691 --> 24:43.442
I'M NOT.
[ CHUCKLES ]

24:43.442 --> 24:45.484
THEIR FIRST REAL IMPRESSION
OF ME.

24:45.484 --> 24:47.446
WHAT HAPPENS AFTER
AT THE HOLIDAYS

24:47.446 --> 24:50.700
WHEN I'M SUDDENLY
NOT PRAYING?

24:50.700 --> 24:52.371
WELL...
[ TONE PLAYS ]

24:52.371 --> 24:54.574
ARE YOU KIDDING ME?
YOU --

24:54.574 --> 24:56.205
Woman: ATTENTION,
LADIES AND GENTLEMEN...
YOU WANT THIS TO GO ON
FOR HOW LONG EXACTLY?

24:56.205 --> 25:00.079
NO, I JUST -- I JUST WANT THEM
TO LIKE YOU AND ACCEPT US.

25:00.079 --> 25:02.291
WELL, IF YOU RESPECT ME,
THEY WILL.

25:02.291 --> 25:04.123
JACKSON. PLEASE.
I --
YOU KNOW WHAT? NO.

25:04.123 --> 25:05.625
APRIL,
THIS CONVERSATION'S OVER.

25:05.625 --> 25:07.717
[ SIGHS ]

25:07.717 --> 25:09.178
EXCUSE ME?

25:09.178 --> 25:11.470
YOU KNEW WHO I WAS
WHEN WE GOT MARRIED.

25:11.470 --> 25:13.052
OKAY?
WE TALKED ABOUT THIS.

25:13.052 --> 25:14.844
WE NEGOTIATED
OUR WHOLE WEDDING AROUND IT.

25:14.844 --> 25:16.435
I THOUGHT THAT WE AGREED

25:16.435 --> 25:18.227
THAT WE WOULD RESPECT
EACH OTHER'S DIFFERENCES.

25:18.227 --> 25:21.190
SO, YEAH, FOR ME,
THIS CONVERSATION'S OVER.

25:21.190 --> 25:22.231
JUST OVER?

25:22.231 --> 25:24.694
YEAH.
I'M DONE WITH IT.

25:24.694 --> 25:26.025
[ SCOFFS ]

25:27.987 --> 25:30.069
MAYBE I DIDN'T --

25:30.069 --> 25:32.361
MAYBE I DIDN'T KNOW
WHO I WAS MARRYING.

25:32.361 --> 25:34.864
REALLY? OKAY.
YEAH, BECAUSE YOU KNOW WHAT?

25:34.864 --> 25:36.746
THE WAY THAT YOU'RE SPEAKING
TO ME RIGHT NOW,

25:36.746 --> 25:38.497
THE WAY THAT YOU'RE ACTING,
IS NOT WHO I MARRIED.

25:38.497 --> 25:40.710
YEAH, I COULD SAY
THE SAME THING.

25:43.042 --> 25:44.834
YOU'RE RIGHT,
BECAUSE YOU KNOW WHAT?

25:44.834 --> 25:46.926
WE THOUGHT ABOUT IT
FOR ALL OF LIKE 18 HOURS.

25:46.926 --> 25:48.467
[ SIGHS ]

25:48.467 --> 25:50.379
WHAT ARE YOU SAYING --
YOU WISH WE HADN'T GOT MARRIED?

25:50.379 --> 25:52.221
[ TONE PLAYS ]
NO.

25:52.221 --> 25:54.093
LADIES AND GENTLEMEN,
MAY I HAVE YOUR ATTENTION?

25:54.093 --> 25:55.845
WE ARE NOW BEGINNING
OUR INITIAL DESCENT

25:55.845 --> 25:57.977
INTO PORT COLUMBUS
INTERNATIONAL AIRPORT.

25:57.977 --> 25:59.388
PLEASE RAISE YOUR TRAY TABLES

25:59.388 --> 26:01.981
AND PLACE YOUR SEATS
IN THE UPRIGHT POSITION.

26:01.981 --> 26:03.893
MY PARENTS
ARE PICKING US UP.

26:03.893 --> 26:06.025
YOU WANT
THE REST OF MY PEANUTS?

26:06.025 --> 26:09.238
I'M ALLERGIC TO PEANUTS.

26:09.238 --> 26:10.690
[ TAPE REWINDING ]

26:10.690 --> 26:12.451
IT LOOKS
LIKE A LOVELY WEDDING.

26:12.451 --> 26:15.154
CONGRATULATIONS AGAIN.

26:15.154 --> 26:18.037
SHE'S A REALLY...
BEAUTIFUL BRIDE.

26:18.037 --> 26:20.289
HMM.

26:20.289 --> 26:21.911
HEY, WHAT'S WRONG?
ARE YOU FEELING PAIN?

26:21.911 --> 26:24.253
NO.
NO. I'M NOT.

26:24.253 --> 26:25.584
IT'S JUST...

26:25.584 --> 26:26.706
LOOK AT ME.

26:26.706 --> 26:28.257
I'M HIDEOUS.

26:28.257 --> 26:30.089
NO.
DO NOT SAY THAT.

26:30.089 --> 26:31.761
NO ONE
WILL EVER LOOK AT ME

26:31.761 --> 26:33.843
THE WAY YOU'RE LOOKING
AT APRIL IN THESE PICTURES.

26:33.843 --> 26:34.884
TATIANA, YOU'RE WRONG.

26:34.884 --> 26:35.975
PLEASE.

26:35.975 --> 26:37.176
OKAY? I LOOK AT YOU,

26:37.176 --> 26:40.389
AND I SEE
SUCH INCREDIBLE STRENGTH.

26:40.389 --> 26:42.601
I SEE BRAVERY.

26:42.601 --> 26:46.605
I SEE
HUMOR AND PERSISTENCE...

26:46.605 --> 26:47.937
BEAUTY.

26:49.819 --> 26:52.732
NOW, THESE SURGERIES, THEY'RE
GONNA GIVE YOU BACK A FACE,

26:52.732 --> 26:55.905
BUT DON'T YOU DARE
FOR A SINGLE MOMENT

26:55.905 --> 26:57.576
THINK THAT YOU'RE NOT
ALREADY BEAUTIFUL.

27:01.791 --> 27:03.502
[ TAPE REWINDING ]

27:03.502 --> 27:05.504
[ CHUCKLES ]

27:05.504 --> 27:07.416
OH, I CAN'T BELIEVE
WE'RE DOING THIS.

27:07.416 --> 27:08.958
I CAN.

27:08.958 --> 27:11.380
YOU MAY NOW KISS.

27:11.380 --> 27:13.963
[ CHUCKLES ]

27:15.965 --> 27:18.057
[ BIRDS CHIRPING ]

27:24.183 --> 27:26.145
[ TAPE REWINDING ]
I KNOW YOU THINK IT'S SILLY.

27:26.145 --> 27:27.606
WELL, I DIDN'T SAY THAT.

27:27.606 --> 27:29.358
BUT I'M SERIOUS, OKAY?

27:29.358 --> 27:31.230
NO PREMARITAL SEX.
[ SIGHS ]

27:31.230 --> 27:33.823
HOW SERIOUS?
LIKE "ABSOLUTELY NOT" SERIOUS

27:33.823 --> 27:36.906
OR "I COULD BE CONVINCED"
SERIOUS?

27:40.910 --> 27:43.873
WE WILL SURVIVE
ONE MORE NIGHT.

27:43.873 --> 27:45.414
[ SIGHS ]
SPEAK FOR YOURSELF.

27:45.414 --> 27:47.456
IF WE WAIT...
MM-HMM.

27:47.456 --> 27:51.050
...OUR WEDDING NIGHT
WILL BE SO AMAZING.

27:51.050 --> 27:52.962
AND TONIGHT
COULD ALSO BE...

27:52.962 --> 27:54.673
so amazing.

27:54.673 --> 27:55.755
[ LAUGHS ]

27:58.597 --> 28:01.510
OKAY.
MM-HMM?

28:01.510 --> 28:02.561
OKAY.
MM-HMM?

28:02.561 --> 28:03.893
MM-HMM.
MM-HMM?

28:03.893 --> 28:05.514
YOU...

28:05.514 --> 28:06.856
WHAT'S THAT?

28:06.856 --> 28:08.227
GOOD NIGHT, JACKSON.

28:08.227 --> 28:10.269
[ SIGHS ]

28:13.692 --> 28:14.904
[ GIGGLES ]

28:17.406 --> 28:20.029
[ BOTH SIGH ]

28:21.620 --> 28:23.953
I'M GONNA GO NOW.

28:26.826 --> 28:28.457
[ CHUCKLES ]
[ LOCK ENGAGES ]

28:42.681 --> 28:44.723
GOOD NIGHT, JACKSON.

28:44.723 --> 28:46.055
YOU PUT THE CHAIN ON?

28:46.055 --> 28:47.306
I'LL SEE YOU
IN THE MORNING.

28:47.306 --> 28:48.187
[ SIGHS ]

28:50.850 --> 28:54.353
[ LOCK ENGAGES ]
ALL RIGHT.

28:54.353 --> 28:56.655
[ LOCK DISENGAGES,
CHAIN RATTLES ]

28:57.356 --> 28:58.157
FORGET SOMETHING?

29:05.074 --> 29:06.125
[ TAPE REWINDING ]

29:06.125 --> 29:07.917
WHAT TIME?
Woman: WHAT ABOUT THIS ONE?

29:07.917 --> 29:11.370
I REALLY HAVE MY HEART SET
ON GETTING MARRIED IN WHITE.

29:11.370 --> 29:13.582
THE WEDDING DRESS
YOU'RE WEARING IS GORGEOUS.

29:13.582 --> 29:15.294
I KNOW A CLEANER
WHO CAN GET THAT STAIN OUT.

29:15.294 --> 29:17.296
YEAH, THANK YOU,
BUT I NEED A NEW DRESS.

29:17.296 --> 29:18.757
I'LL SEE
WHAT I HAVE IN THE BACK.

29:18.757 --> 29:20.759
THANK YOU.
THANK YOU.

29:20.759 --> 29:22.551
YES, THANK YOU.
BYE.

29:22.551 --> 29:24.383
ALL RIGHT.

29:24.383 --> 29:26.145
WE'VE GOT OURSELVES
A JUSTICE OF THE PEACE.

29:26.145 --> 29:28.057
TOMORROW AFTERNOON,
HE WILL MARRY US.

29:28.057 --> 29:29.518
UH,
A JUSTICE OF THE PEACE?

29:29.518 --> 29:30.559
MM-HMM.

29:30.559 --> 29:32.481
OKAY, SO, UM...

29:32.481 --> 29:33.853
OUR WEDDING WILL BE...

29:33.853 --> 29:35.154
LEGAL. YEAH.

29:35.154 --> 29:36.695
HE'S GOT A LICENSE.

29:36.695 --> 29:39.108
HE'S NOT AN ELVIS
OR A PIRATE

29:39.108 --> 29:40.529
OR A CARTOON CHARACTER.

29:40.529 --> 29:44.994
I-I -- I HAD JUST REALLY HOPED
THAT WE'D FIND A MINISTER.

29:44.994 --> 29:47.116
SOMEONE NONDENOMINATIONAL,
OBVIOUSLY,

29:47.116 --> 29:48.747
BUT, YOU KNOW, JUST SOMEONE
WHO'S AT LEAST BEEN ORDAINED.

29:48.747 --> 29:50.669
APRIL, I'M NOT RELIGIOUS.

29:50.669 --> 29:51.750
NO, I KNOW, I KNOW.

29:51.750 --> 29:53.002
JUST HAVING SOMEONE

29:53.002 --> 29:54.673
WITH SOME SORT OF RELATIONSHIP
WITH GOD MARRY US

29:54.673 --> 29:55.965
IS KIND OF IMPORTANT TO ME.

29:55.965 --> 29:57.176
I MEAN,
EVEN FINDING THIS GUY

29:57.176 --> 29:58.587
WASN'T EASY
ON SUCH SHORT NOTICE.

29:58.587 --> 30:01.720
I MEAN, HAVING A WEDDING
WITHOUT A LOT OF GOD TALK

30:01.720 --> 30:02.882
IS KIND OF IMPORTANT
TO ME.

30:04.844 --> 30:06.886
I ALWAYS HAD SUCH, LIKE,
A CLEAR IDEA

30:06.886 --> 30:08.347
OF WHAT MY WEDDING
WOULD LOOK LIKE.

30:08.347 --> 30:11.981
WANT ME TO BRING YOU BACK
TO THE BARN, OR WERE YOU --

30:11.981 --> 30:15.064
NO!
STOP IT, JACKSON. NO.

30:15.064 --> 30:17.937
[ INHALES DEEPLY ]

30:17.937 --> 30:21.360
I JUST WANT GOD
AT MY WEDDING.

30:21.360 --> 30:23.993
I WANT HIM THERE FOR THE MOST
IMPORTANT DAY OF MY LIFE.

30:23.993 --> 30:25.865
WELL, YOU KNOW
THAT AFTER WE GET MARRIED,

30:25.865 --> 30:28.657
I'M NOT GONNA TURN
INTO THIS CHURCHGOING GUY.

30:28.657 --> 30:30.659
YOU KNOW,
I WATCH FOOTBALL ON SUNDAYS.

30:30.659 --> 30:33.412
YOU ARE NOT CHANGING
WHO YOU ARE,

30:33.412 --> 30:37.086
AND I DO NOT WANT YOU TO.

30:37.086 --> 30:39.838
BUT YOU CAN'T EXPECT ME
TO CHANGE WHO I AM, EITHER.

30:39.838 --> 30:42.421
[ FOOTSTEPS APPROACHING ]
Woman: HOW'S THIS ONE?

30:42.421 --> 30:43.923
OH.

30:43.923 --> 30:45.304
RIGHT IDEA, WRONG COLOR.

30:48.968 --> 30:51.020
OKAY.
YEAH?

30:51.020 --> 30:52.181
I'LL MAKE
SOME PHONE CALLS,

30:52.181 --> 30:53.732
AND WE'LL FIND
AN ORDAINED MINISTER.

30:53.732 --> 30:54.894
THANK YOU.
MM-HMM.

30:57.816 --> 30:59.398
DID YOU SEE
WHAT WE JUST DID THERE?

30:59.398 --> 31:00.399
WE DISAGREED.

31:00.399 --> 31:01.570
WE DISCUSSED.

31:01.570 --> 31:03.282
WE COMPROMISED.

31:03.282 --> 31:04.984
WE ARE PRETTY AMAZING
AT THIS MARRIAGE THING.

31:04.984 --> 31:06.575
[ Laughing ] WE ARE.
THIS ONE?

31:06.575 --> 31:07.987
[ GASPS ] OH, MY GOSH!

31:07.987 --> 31:08.988
OH, MY GOSH!
OH!

31:08.988 --> 31:10.119
NO, NO, NO, NO, NO!
DON'T LOOK!

31:10.119 --> 31:11.580
IT'S BAD LUCK!
IT'S BAD LUCK! [ SQUEALS ]

31:11.580 --> 31:12.912
YES, YES, YES!
[ SQUEALS ]

31:15.834 --> 31:17.626
[ TAPE REWINDING ]

31:17.626 --> 31:19.418
NO, NO, WAIT.
YOU CAN'T STEAL ALL MY FRIES.

31:19.418 --> 31:20.709
SURE, I CAN.
WHAT'S MINE IS YOURS.

31:20.709 --> 31:21.921
WHAT'S YOURS IS MINE.

31:21.921 --> 31:23.002
WE'RE NOT MARRIED YET.

31:23.002 --> 31:24.213
[ LAUGHS ]

31:24.213 --> 31:25.634
OH! OOH!
AW, CRAP.

31:25.634 --> 31:27.466
SORRY. CRAP, CRAP, CRAP.
OH, NO! AAH!

31:27.466 --> 31:28.637
YOU KNOW WHAT?
NO MORE FRIES FOR YOU.

31:28.637 --> 31:29.768
IT WAS AN ACCIDENT.

31:29.768 --> 31:31.560
NO, NO.
NO MORE.

31:31.560 --> 31:32.771
[ LAUGHS ]

31:32.771 --> 31:34.563
HEY.

31:34.563 --> 31:35.975
WHERE ARE WE GONNA LIVE?

31:35.975 --> 31:37.226
AFTER?

31:37.226 --> 31:41.150
WELL, I WAS THINKING...
WHAT ABOUT MY PLACE?

31:41.150 --> 31:43.612
ABSOLUTELY.

31:43.612 --> 31:45.114
REALLY?
YEAH.

31:45.114 --> 31:46.485
IT'S WAY NICER. IT'S BIGGER.
IT'S PERFECT.

31:46.485 --> 31:47.866
GREAT.

31:47.866 --> 31:50.159
BUT I'M NOT CHANGING
MY NAME.

31:50.159 --> 31:51.830
WHAT?
AVERY'S A GREAT NAME.

31:51.830 --> 31:53.122
SO IS KEPNER.
YOU WANT TO TAKE IT?

31:53.122 --> 31:54.453
SURE.
REALLY?

31:54.453 --> 31:56.205
NO. [ LAUGHS ]

31:56.205 --> 31:57.706
[ Laughing ]
NO, I'M NOT CHANGING MY NAME.

31:57.706 --> 31:59.338
[ Laughter ] OKAY.

31:59.338 --> 32:01.170
I DIDN'T EXPECT YOU TO,
EITHER.

32:01.170 --> 32:02.591
THAT'S NOT REALLY A THING
FOR ME.

32:02.591 --> 32:03.752
IT'S NOT?

32:03.752 --> 32:04.883
NO, DEFINITELY NOT.

32:04.883 --> 32:06.755
[ SNICKERS ]

32:06.755 --> 32:08.807
[ Laughing ] WHAT?

32:08.807 --> 32:09.888
HOLY CRAP.

32:09.888 --> 32:11.971
WE DID THIS!

32:11.971 --> 32:13.552
WE ARE DOING THIS.
WE'RE DOING THIS.

32:20.319 --> 32:21.520
[ TAPE REWINDING ]

32:23.732 --> 32:25.774
[ CHURCH BELL TOLLING ]

32:25.774 --> 32:29.568
♪♪

32:47.846 --> 32:48.887
Jackson: I LOVE YOU.
I ALWAYS HAVE.

32:48.887 --> 32:49.848
EVEN THE THINGS I DON'T LIKE,
I LOVE.

32:49.848 --> 32:51.300
YOU'RE GETTING MARRIED?

32:51.300 --> 32:53.552
UNLESS YOU CAN GIVE ME
A REASON NOT TO.

32:53.552 --> 32:54.723
[ TAPE REWINDING ]

32:54.723 --> 32:56.555
LOOK, WE'RE NOT DOING THIS
ANYMORE, OKAY?

32:56.555 --> 32:58.517
NO MORE SCREWING IN CLOSETS.
NO MORE SCREWING ANYWHERE.

32:58.517 --> 33:00.649
I TOLD YOU --
LAST TIME WAS THE LAST TIME.

33:00.649 --> 33:02.101
[ SIGHS ]

33:02.101 --> 33:04.193
HEY.
WHAT'S WRONG?

33:04.193 --> 33:06.735
I AM SUPPOSED TO DO
A FACIAL REANIMATION SURGERY.

33:06.735 --> 33:09.368
A PROCEDURE SLOAN PRACTICALLY
INVENTED MY THIRD YEAR.

33:09.368 --> 33:11.160
DONE IT WITH HIM
LIKE A HANDFUL OF TIMES.

33:11.160 --> 33:13.162
I MEAN, I NEVER --
[ SIGHS ]

33:13.162 --> 33:14.533
THERE'S NO WAY
I CAN DO THIS ON MY OWN.

33:14.533 --> 33:16.415
OF COURSE YOU CAN.
NO, YOU HAVEN'T SEEN HIM DO IT.

33:16.415 --> 33:18.667
HE'S BRILLIANT, OKAY,
AND SO PRECISE.

33:18.667 --> 33:20.539
I JUST NEEDED MORE TIME.

33:20.539 --> 33:22.251
YOU CAN DO THIS, JACKSON.

33:22.251 --> 33:24.793
APRIL, WHAT IF I CAN'T?
WHAT IF I MAKE HER WORSE?

33:24.793 --> 33:26.175
THIS WOMAN'S COUNTING ON ME,

33:26.175 --> 33:28.427
AND I PROMISED
THAT I COULD HELP.

33:28.427 --> 33:30.589
THEN YOU WILL.
YOU WILL.

33:30.589 --> 33:33.552
I KNOW YOU WILL.

33:33.552 --> 33:35.974
YOU ARE NOT A PERSON WHO MAKES
PROMISES HE DOESN'T KEEP.

33:38.557 --> 33:39.728
[ TAPE REWINDING ]
OKAY, LET'S PUSH 10
OF MORPHINE.

33:39.728 --> 33:41.060
[ SOBBING ]
YEAH.

33:41.060 --> 33:43.772
-WHAT DO WE GOT?
-TATIANA FLAUTO, 30s.

33:43.772 --> 33:46.195
SOME PSYCHO
THREW ACID ON HER FACE.

33:46.195 --> 33:47.526
POLICE GOT HIM, THOUGH.

33:47.526 --> 33:49.608
A GOOD SAMARITAN GAVE HER
A TOWEL WITH ICE IN IT

33:49.608 --> 33:50.739
BEFORE THE PARAMEDICS
GOT THERE.

33:50.739 --> 33:52.451
AND IT ADHERED TO THE BURNS.

33:52.451 --> 33:53.992
WE HAVEN'T BEEN ABLE
TO SEE UNDERNEATH.

33:53.992 --> 33:55.494
RIGHT. ALL RIGHT, LET'S START
WITH A BOTTLE OF SALINE, PLEASE.

33:55.494 --> 33:56.705
[ Crying ] NO.

33:56.705 --> 33:58.577
THANK YOU.

33:58.577 --> 34:01.080
HI. TATIANA, IS IT?
MY NAME IS DR. AVERY.

34:01.080 --> 34:03.162
I'D LIKE TO WET THIS TOWEL
WITH SALINE

34:03.162 --> 34:04.213
SO IT'LL COME OFF EASIER,
OKAY?

34:04.213 --> 34:05.214
WILL YOU LET ME DO THAT?

34:05.214 --> 34:06.625
I'M SCARED, I'M SCARED!
OKAY.

34:06.625 --> 34:08.377
I KNOW. I KNOW.
IT'S OKAY. IT'S ALL RIGHT.

34:08.377 --> 34:10.169
YOU'RE SAFE NOW, OKAY?
YOU'RE SAFE HERE.

34:10.169 --> 34:11.510
I JUST NEED YOU
TO KEEP STILL

34:11.510 --> 34:12.841
SO THAT I CAN GET A LOOK
AT WHAT'S GOING ON.

34:12.841 --> 34:14.093
ALL RIGHT?
NO, NO, NO!

34:14.093 --> 34:15.434
I KNOW.
IT'S OKAY. YOU'RE OKAY.

34:15.434 --> 34:16.805
NO, NO, NO!
YOU'RE OKAY.
I'M GONNA HELP YOU.

34:16.805 --> 34:17.806
HERE COMES THE SALINE.

34:17.806 --> 34:18.887
[ WHIMPERS ]
NO, NO, NO, NO!

34:18.887 --> 34:20.679
OKAY. HERE WE GO.
NO! NO! NO!

34:20.679 --> 34:22.481
ALL RIGHT, IT'S OKAY.

34:22.481 --> 34:23.852
-OKAY. OKAY.
-OKAY.

34:23.852 --> 34:25.274
NO, NO, NO!
REALLY GOOD.

34:25.274 --> 34:26.645
NOW WE GOT TO REMOVE
THIS TOWEL, OKAY?

34:26.645 --> 34:28.066
WE'RE GONNA GET STARTED.
IT'S GONNA HURT.

34:28.066 --> 34:29.778
SO I NEED YOU TO TAKE
A DEEP BREATH FOR ME, OKAY?

34:29.778 --> 34:31.150
DEEP BREATH.
[ SOBBING LOUDLY ]

34:31.150 --> 34:32.281
-HERE WE GO. ALL RIGHT.
-OKAY.

34:32.281 --> 34:34.193
NO! NO!

34:34.193 --> 34:35.404
IT'S OKAY.

34:35.404 --> 34:37.576
[ SOBBING ]

34:37.576 --> 34:38.787
YOU'RE DOING GREAT.

34:38.787 --> 34:39.828
OKAY.

34:39.828 --> 34:41.460
ALL DONE.
YOU DID GREAT.

34:41.460 --> 34:43.252
YOU DID GREAT.

34:43.252 --> 34:45.374
UH, WE NEED TO GET SLOAN
DOWN HERE IMMEDIATELY.

34:45.374 --> 34:48.587
UH, SLOAN IS ON A PLANE
TO IDAHO RIGHT NOW.

34:48.587 --> 34:49.878
CAN YOU HANDLE THIS?

34:49.878 --> 34:51.590
BREATHE.
WHAT IS IT? WHAT'S WRONG?

34:51.590 --> 34:52.841
IT'S TOO BAD!
YOU CAN'T FIX MY FACE!

34:52.841 --> 34:53.842
-NO, NO. NO, NO, NO, NO.
-NO, NO, NO!

34:53.842 --> 34:55.093
-OKAY.
-NO, TATIANA, HEY.

34:55.093 --> 34:57.426
I KNOW THAT WE JUST MET,
ALL RIGHT?

34:57.426 --> 34:59.428
BUT WHAT YOU DON'T KNOW
IS THAT YOU AND I,

34:59.428 --> 35:01.520
WE ARE A TEAM NOW.

35:01.520 --> 35:03.682
IT'S GONNA BE YOU AND ME.
WE'RE GONNA GET THROUGH
THIS TOGETHER, ALL RIGHT?

35:03.682 --> 35:05.023
I'M NOT GONNA LIE.
IT'S NOT GONNA BE EASY,

35:05.023 --> 35:06.395
AND IT'S NOT GONNA BE QUICK,

35:06.395 --> 35:08.357
BUT I'M GONNA BE RIGHT HERE
THE ENTIRE TIME, OKAY?

35:08.357 --> 35:10.689
I WILL NOT LEAVE YOUR SIDE.

35:10.689 --> 35:12.781
I PROMISE YOU.

35:12.781 --> 35:14.693
OKAY?

35:14.693 --> 35:16.535
ALL RIGHT.

35:16.535 --> 35:18.157
LET'S GET MEPITEL
AND XEROFORM, PLEASE.
OH.

35:18.157 --> 35:20.909
JACKSON. HEY.

35:20.909 --> 35:23.202
IT'S OKAY.
REALLY.

35:23.202 --> 35:25.504
I LOST SOME -- SOME FRIENDS
THAT DAY.

35:25.504 --> 35:27.546
I HATE SLOAN.

35:27.546 --> 35:29.958
EVEN WHEN I'M PERFECT, HE TALKS
TO ME LIKE I'M AN IDIOT.

35:29.958 --> 35:32.801
WELL, TRY SPENDING A DAY IN THE
E.R. WITH DR. MAJOR OWEN HUNT.

35:32.801 --> 35:33.962
THAT MAN IS DARK.

35:33.962 --> 35:37.306
HE IS A DARK,
PIG-STABBING, SCARY MAN.

35:37.306 --> 35:38.757
WHAT?

35:38.757 --> 35:42.601
WHAT'S THE MATTER?

35:42.601 --> 35:45.604
THIS IS
WHERE REED WAS SHOT...

35:45.604 --> 35:47.145
WHERE I FOUND HER.

35:47.145 --> 35:49.398
I SLIPPED IN HER BLOOD
RIGHT THERE.

35:49.398 --> 35:50.939
I HAVEN'T BEEN
BACK HERE SINCE.

35:53.322 --> 35:57.446
THERE'S AN ELEVATOR UPSTAIRS
NEAR WHERE CHARLES DIED.

35:57.446 --> 35:59.618
I NEVER USE IT.

35:59.618 --> 36:02.411
[ BREATHING HEAVILY ]

36:04.663 --> 36:06.335
HEY.

36:06.335 --> 36:08.497
YOU -- YOU OKAY?
HEY.

36:08.497 --> 36:11.500
OH. OKAY.

36:11.500 --> 36:13.171
I KNOW. I KNOW.

36:13.171 --> 36:15.884
OKAY?
WE'RE -- WE'RE HERE.

36:15.884 --> 36:17.756
WE'RE OKAY.
[ Voice breaking ]
I HAD A GUN POINTED AT ME.

36:17.756 --> 36:19.848
I KNOW. I KNOW.

36:19.848 --> 36:22.010
MY LIFE
FLASHED BEFORE MY EYES.

36:22.010 --> 36:24.433
IT -- IT -- IT REALLY DID.
Shh. OKAY.

36:24.433 --> 36:27.436
AND IT WAS SO...

36:27.436 --> 36:29.568
BORING!

36:29.568 --> 36:32.150
[ CHUCKLES ]

36:32.150 --> 36:35.524
I JUST KEPT THINKING,
"I DON'T WANT TO DIE A VIRGIN."

36:35.524 --> 36:38.487
OH.

36:38.487 --> 36:41.580
YOU CAN FIX THAT.

36:41.580 --> 36:43.782
WAS THAT A PROPOSITION?

36:43.782 --> 36:45.163
NO, I MEANT --
OH, OH!

36:45.163 --> 36:46.875
NO! NO, NO, NO, NO.
I-I DIDN'T MEAN --

36:46.875 --> 36:47.956
NO, I -- NO.

36:47.956 --> 36:49.588
I WAS -- I -- IT WAS A JOKE.
YEAH.

36:49.588 --> 36:51.460
I WAS MAKING
A TOTALLY STUPID JOKE.

36:51.460 --> 36:52.421
YEAH, IT WASN'T GOOD.
YEAH.

36:52.421 --> 36:53.882
OKAY. I'M...

36:53.882 --> 36:55.634
[ CLEARS THROAT ]
EN--

36:55.634 --> 36:56.675
WHAT?
GOOD LUCK WITH SLOAN.

36:56.675 --> 36:58.257
MM-HMM, MM-HMM.

36:59.758 --> 37:01.720
[ CLICKS TONGUE ]

37:01.720 --> 37:04.393
WELL, THAT GIRL IS WEIRD.

37:04.393 --> 37:05.474
[ TAPE REWINDING ]

37:05.474 --> 37:07.266
[ GUNSHOT, BODY THUDS ]

37:07.266 --> 37:09.308
I'M A VIRGIN.
YES. SO WHAT?

37:09.308 --> 37:10.559
IT'S NOT SOMETHING
I TALK ABOUT, OKAY?

37:10.559 --> 37:12.311
WE ALL HAVE THINGS
WE DON'T TALK ABOUT.

37:12.311 --> 37:14.313
SHE THINKS
YOUR HUSBAND WALKS ON WATER.

37:14.313 --> 37:16.024
[ TAPE REWINDING ]

37:16.024 --> 37:17.115
Woman:
CINCINNATI, OHIO, PEDIATRICS.

37:17.115 --> 37:18.447
THANK YOU.

37:18.447 --> 37:19.988
WHO'S NEXT?

37:19.988 --> 37:22.120
UH, I'LL GO.

37:22.120 --> 37:25.284
UH, CHARLES PERCY,
BROOKINGS, SOUTH DAKOTA.

37:25.284 --> 37:27.075
I WANT TO BE
A TRAUMA SURGEON.

37:27.075 --> 37:29.628
OR MAYBE VASCULAR.

37:29.628 --> 37:32.170
OR -- OR, LIKE, UH...

37:32.170 --> 37:34.172
I DON'T KNOW, ACTUALLY.
UH...

37:34.172 --> 37:35.674
ALL RIGHT, WELL,
YOU'VE GOT A LOT OF TIME

37:35.674 --> 37:36.835
TO FIGURE THAT ONE OUT.

37:36.835 --> 37:37.926
WHO'S NEXT?

37:38.677 --> 37:40.299
UH, RIGHT HERE.

37:40.299 --> 37:41.840
JACKSON AVERY,
ORIGINALLY FROM BOSTON --

37:41.840 --> 37:43.181
OH, H-H-HOLD ON.
WHAT?

37:43.181 --> 37:45.884
LIKE
"HARPER AVERY" AVERY?

37:45.884 --> 37:48.727
UH, YEAH, ACTUALLY.

37:48.727 --> 37:50.098
ANYWAY --

37:50.098 --> 37:51.730
SO YOU'RE, LIKE,
BORN TO THE THRONE.

37:51.730 --> 37:53.151
[ SIGHS ] YOU KNOW WHAT?
I WOULDN'T --

37:53.151 --> 37:55.153
April: DO YOU KNOW A
CATHERINE AVERY, THE UROLOGIST?

37:55.153 --> 37:56.735
I DO, ACTUALLY.

37:56.735 --> 37:57.776
ARE YOU WRITING THIS DOWN?

37:57.776 --> 37:59.277
SHE'S JUST, LIKE, AMAZING.

37:59.277 --> 38:00.609
ARE YOU
GOING INTO UROLOGY, TOO?

38:00.609 --> 38:02.361
NO.
CARDIOTHORACIC ALL THE WAY.

38:02.361 --> 38:03.532
CAN I BE DONE NOW?

38:03.532 --> 38:05.784
I'LL GO!

38:05.784 --> 38:07.406
HI.
I'M APRIL KEPNER.

38:07.406 --> 38:08.667
I'M FROM OHIO,

38:08.667 --> 38:10.619
AND I'M SUPER-EXCITED
TO BE NEAR THE OCEAN,

38:10.619 --> 38:12.210
ALTHOUGH I DON'T REALLY KNOW
HOW I FEEL ABOUT THE RAIN YET.

38:12.210 --> 38:13.502
AS FAR AS SPECIALTY GOES,

38:13.502 --> 38:15.083
I'M LOOKING FOR SOMETHING
WITH SET HOURS

38:15.083 --> 38:17.005
SO THAT I CAN RAISE KIDS
EVENTUALLY --

38:17.005 --> 38:18.837
TWO BOYS AND A GIRL.

38:18.837 --> 38:20.969
SO I'M THINKING PLASTICS,
UROLOGY, PROCTOLOGY.
♪ AND WHEN I... ♪

38:20.969 --> 38:23.011
I ALSO GREW UP ON A FARM...
WE TALK ABOUT THE MECHANISM
OF INJURY...

38:23.011 --> 38:25.223
...SO I CAN GUT AND BLEED
A 220-POUND BUTCHER HOG...
...ABOUT WHERE IT ALL STARTED.

38:25.223 --> 38:27.135
...IN UNDER THREE MINUTES.
BUT THE TRUTH IS...

38:27.135 --> 38:28.597
EYES CLOSED.
...IT'S SORT OF A MYTH.

38:28.597 --> 38:33.191
WE CAN'T BOIL EVERY INJURY
DOWN TO ONE SINGLE BLOW.

38:33.191 --> 38:36.985
♪ FALL IN LOVE ♪

38:36.985 --> 38:41.820
♪ IN A SINGLE TOUCH ♪

38:41.820 --> 38:46.905
♪ AND FALL APART
WHEN IT HURTS TOO MUCH? ♪

38:51.370 --> 38:55.794
♪ CAN WE SKIP PAST ♪

38:55.794 --> 38:59.918
♪ NEAR-DEATH CLICHéS ♪

38:59.918 --> 39:03.091
♪ WHERE MY HEART RESTARTS ♪

39:03.091 --> 39:06.264
♪ AS MY LIFE REPLAYS? ♪

39:06.264 --> 39:09.928
♪ ALL I WANT ♪

39:09.928 --> 39:14.142
♪ IS TO FLIP A SWITCH ♪
THIS IS ONE OF THE SIMPLER
DIVORCES I'VE SEEN, ACTUALLY.

39:14.142 --> 39:18.607
♪ BEFORE SOMETHING BREAKS
THAT CANNOT BE FIXED ♪

39:18.607 --> 39:19.688
YOU WANT THIS?

39:22.571 --> 39:24.653
DO YOU REALLY WANT THIS?

39:24.653 --> 39:29.578
♪ I KNOW,
I KNOW THE SIRENS SOUND ♪

39:29.578 --> 39:33.452
♪ JUST BEFORE
THE WALLS COME DOWN ♪

39:33.452 --> 39:36.415
♪ PAIN'S A WELL-INTENTIONED
WEATHERMAN ♪

39:36.415 --> 39:37.626
OKAY.

39:37.626 --> 39:39.918
WHAT HURTS US IS CUMULATIVE.

39:39.918 --> 39:41.460
♪ PREDICTING GOD
AS BEST HE CAN ♪
IT HAPPENS OVER TIME.

39:41.460 --> 39:45.133
WE ABSORB BLOW AFTER BLOW...

39:45.133 --> 39:49.217
♪ BUT, GOD,
I WANT TO FEEL AGAIN ♪
...SHOCK AFTER SHOCK,
PAINFUL HIT AFTER HIT.

40:05.524 --> 40:09.738
♪ RAIN OR SHINE ♪

40:09.738 --> 40:12.120
♪ I DON'T FEEL A THING ♪

40:12.120 --> 40:13.291
IS THERE ANYTHING ELSE?

40:13.291 --> 40:15.083
UH, THAT'S IT.
NO.

40:15.083 --> 40:17.295
♪ JUST SOME INFORMATION ♪
OKAY, THEN.

40:17.295 --> 40:22.210
♪ UPON MY SKIN ♪

40:22.210 --> 40:25.173
♪ I MISS THE SUBTLE ACHES ♪
BUT EVEN THEN...

40:25.173 --> 40:28.136
EVEN IF WE KNOW
EXACTLY HOW WE GOT HERE...

40:28.136 --> 40:30.218
♪ WHEN THE WEATHER CHANGED ♪
...IT DOESN'T MEAN
WE CAN FIX IT.

40:30.218 --> 40:31.510
Tatiana:
TOO LATE TO BACK OUT?

40:31.510 --> 40:32.811
ARE YOU KIDDING ME?
OH!

40:32.811 --> 40:35.814
TIMOTHY AND I
HAD A HUGE FIGHT THIS MORNING.

40:35.814 --> 40:36.855
IT WAS PROBABLY MY FAULT.

40:36.855 --> 40:38.817
WELL, YEAH, WITH THAT MOUTH,
PROBABLY WAS.

40:38.817 --> 40:41.269
♪ ALL I WANT ♪
LOOK, YOU GUYS
ARE GONNA FIGHT, OKAY?

40:41.269 --> 40:43.522
YOU'LL PROBABLY HAVE
THAT SAME FIGHT FOR 50 YEARS.

40:43.522 --> 40:47.195
♪ IS TO FLIP THE SWITCH ♪
BUT YOU JUST CAN'T LET IT BECOME
BIGGER THAN THE TWO OF YOU.

40:47.195 --> 40:49.157
♪ BEFORE SOMETHING BREAKS ♪
SO, IN OTHER WORDS,
MARRIAGE IS HARD...

40:49.157 --> 40:50.779
♪ THAT CANNOT BE FIXED ♪
...BUT NOT AS HARD AS GETTING
ACID THROWN IN YOUR FACE?

40:50.779 --> 40:52.120
YES.

40:52.120 --> 40:54.032
THIS MOUTH.
YOU SEE? FOUR YEARS OF THIS.

40:54.032 --> 40:57.035
AND YET YOU STILL AGREED
TO WALK ME DOWN THE AISLE.

40:57.035 --> 40:59.077
YOU KEPT EVERY PROMISE
YOU MADE TO ME.

40:59.077 --> 41:02.130
THANK YOU.

41:02.130 --> 41:04.042
MM-HMM.

41:04.042 --> 41:06.925
I'M SORRY
ABOUT YOU AND APRIL.

41:06.925 --> 41:07.926
NO.

41:07.926 --> 41:10.258
TODAY'S ABOUT YOU, OKAY?

41:10.258 --> 41:12.050
LET'S GET YOU MARRIED.

41:12.050 --> 41:14.142
HMM?

41:14.142 --> 41:15.473
♪ JUST BEFORE THE WALLS
COME DOWN ♪
FOR YOU.

41:15.473 --> 41:16.725
[ CHUCKLES ]

41:16.725 --> 41:18.517
YOU CAN'T HEAL EVERY WOUND.

41:18.517 --> 41:21.019
♪ PAIN'S A WELL-INTENTIONED
WEATHERMAN ♪
AND THAT'S OKAY.

41:21.019 --> 41:24.192
I HAVE TO BELIEVE IT'S OKAY.

41:24.192 --> 41:25.774
♪ PREDICTING GOD
AS BEST HE CAN ♪

41:25.774 --> 41:26.945
HEY!

41:26.945 --> 41:28.527
OH.

41:28.527 --> 41:30.569
I WASN'T SURE WHAT YOU WOULD BE
IN THE MOOD FOR,

41:30.569 --> 41:32.110
SO I KIND OF
GOT EVERYTHING.

41:32.110 --> 41:35.704
CHAMPAGNE, TEQUILA,
PINOT NOIR --

41:35.704 --> 41:37.876
PICK YOUR POISON.

41:37.876 --> 41:39.457
NO, THANKS.

41:39.457 --> 41:40.829
♪ DOWN MY ARMS ♪
HUH?
WHAT'S HAPPENING?

41:40.829 --> 41:43.171
DID YOU ALREADY START DRINKING?
ARE YOU -- ARE YOU DRUNK?

41:43.171 --> 41:45.924
♪ A THOUSAND SATELLITES ♪
WHAT? I'M...

41:45.924 --> 41:48.086
HUNGRY, MAYBE.
WHAT?

41:48.086 --> 41:49.427
♪ SUDDENLY DISCOVER ♪
YOU JUST SIGNED
DIVORCE PAPERS,

41:49.427 --> 41:50.629
AND YOU DON'T WANT
A DRINK?

41:50.629 --> 41:52.090
WHAT ARE YOU --
WHAT ARE YOU, PREGNANT?

41:52.090 --> 41:53.722
♪ SIGNS OF LIFE ♪
[ CHUCKLES ]

41:53.722 --> 41:55.804
WHAT?

41:57.395 --> 41:59.137
OH.

41:59.137 --> 42:00.478
APRIL.

42:00.478 --> 42:02.561
I HAVE TO BELIEVE
THAT EVEN IF SOMETHING

42:02.561 --> 42:04.693
SEEMS LIKE
IT CANNOT BE FIXED...

42:06.905 --> 42:10.488
ACCORDING TO THE TEST
I TOOK THIS MORNING,

42:10.488 --> 42:14.452
YEAH, ACTUALLY.

42:14.452 --> 42:16.454
I THINK I AM.

42:16.454 --> 42:18.326
...IT DOESN'T MEAN IT'S BROKEN.
